to him?

16:21.689 --> 16:25.401
Would you say relations,
uh, the dialogue is cordial?

16:28.237 --> 16:30.239
Do they see each other visually
when they talk?

17:11.572 --> 17:13.157
Yes. May I-- So this is
just a trivial question,

17:13.157 --> 17:15.076
I've always been curious.
Do they call each other

17:15.076 --> 17:18.162
Vladimir and Barack?
Or do they call--

17:20.998 --> 17:24.126
First name?
That's great.

17:24.126 --> 17:28.005
Can we talk about
outside influences
in this Ukraine story now?

17:28.005 --> 17:32.009
We know the about the NGOs
that were operating in Ukraine.

17:32.009 --> 17:37.932
We know that Victoria Nuland,
the undersecretary of state
for Eastern Europe,

17:37.932 --> 17:40.184
<i>was very active supporting</i>
<i>change in government.</i>

17:40.184 --> 17:44.188
Good to see you.
We're here from America.

17:44.188 --> 17:46.399
Would you like some bread?
Please, take something. Please.

17:46.399 --> 17:50.194
Nuland:
<i>We've invested</i>
<i>over five billion dollars</i>

17:50.194 --> 17:52.697
to assist Ukraine in these
and other goals

17:52.697 --> 17:57.034
that will ensure
a secure and prosperous
and democratic Ukraine.

17:57.034 --> 17:59.078
Stone: <i>We know that</i>
<i>Senator John McCain,</i>

17:59.078 --> 18:03.124
<i>visited and was seen at rallies</i>

18:03.124 --> 18:07.253
<i>with extremist leaders,</i>
<i>including some neo-Nazis.</i>

18:07.253 --> 18:10.965
This is about the future
you want for your country.

18:10.965 --> 18:13.801
This is about the future
you deserve.

18:15.219 --> 18:17.513
Stone:
<i>We know that America</i>

18:17.513 --> 18:19.223
<i>and the National Endowment</i>
<i>for Democracy,</i>

18:19.223 --> 18:22.602
<i>which is a, uh, also</i>
<i>a very influential pr--</i>

18:22.602 --> 18:29.900
a non-profit, private NGO,
was very active,
very active here.

18:29.900 --> 18:34.530
<i>Carl Gershman,</i>
<i>who was the president of it,</i>
<i>made very strong speeches,</i>

18:34.530 --> 18:36.824
<i>uh, he wanted</i>
<i>an independent Ukraine.</i>

18:36.824 --> 18:40.036
And we know
that the Hungarian
billionaire hedge funder,

18:40.036 --> 18:44.332
<i>George Soros was also</i>
<i>very involved in supporting</i>

18:44.332 --> 18:46.500
<i>the groups from here,</i>
<i>in Ukraine.</i>

18:47.585 --> 18:50.046
(chuckles)

19:10.107 --> 19:11.192
In other words,
United States can unite--

19:11.192 --> 19:15.196
can keep a united
pro-American Europe,

19:15.196 --> 19:18.366
and NATO,
with an external enemy
such as Russia.

19:28.125 --> 19:30.419
Joe Biden:
<i>The final assault came</i>

19:30.419 --> 19:31.379
amidst fire and ice,

19:33.297 --> 19:36.384
snipers on rooftops.

19:36.384 --> 19:40.471
The Heavenly Hundred paid
the ultimate price of patriots
the world over.

19:42.932 --> 19:45.893
Their blood and courage

19:45.893 --> 19:50.356
delivering
to the Ukrainian people
a second chance for freedom.

19:50.940 --> 19:53.275
<i>Their sacrifice...</i>

19:55.027 --> 19:57.196
to put it bluntly,

19:57.196 --> 20:00.116
is now your obligation.

20:01.992 --> 20:03.911
Stone:
<i>In hindsight, looking back,</i>

20:03.911 --> 20:07.289
<i>did you make a mistake</i>
<i>by annexing Crimea?</i>

20:07.289 --> 20:08.582
<i>Because it cost you</i>
<i>tremendously.</i>

20:08.582 --> 20:13.754
The sanctions, the whole
East EU turns on Russia, the US.

20:13.754 --> 20:17.591
It becomes big news,
because it's... it's illegal.

20:17.591 --> 20:20.928
It's regarded as illegal
in the international
post-war treaty world.

20:20.928 --> 20:21.721
(chuckles)

20:21.721 --> 20:23.973
(coughs)

21:18.611 --> 21:20.404
(crowd chanting)

21:23.574 --> 21:24.450
(Putin speaking)

21:54.730 --> 21:58.609
<i>But it does raise questions</i>
<i>on whether this vote really</i>
<i>is free and fair,</i>

21:58.609 --> 22:01.946
<i>especially given the heavy</i>
<i>military presence in Crimea</i>
<i>right now. Errol?</i>

22:02.822 --> 22:04.490
(Putin speaking)

22:32.893 --> 22:35.604
More than 95 percent voted
to become part of Russia.

22:35.604 --> 22:37.815
Officials said there was
an unprecedented turnout,

22:37.815 --> 22:40.693
with at least eight
of ten eligible Crimeans
having their say.

23:56.936 --> 24:01.273
Stone:
But economically, as you say,
you're self-sufficient.

24:01.273 --> 24:05.569
They're gone.
Let them have their problems.

24:05.569 --> 24:07.613
It's not gonna destroy
your country.

24:11.200 --> 24:13.077
And at one point, you told me
in our last, uh, meeting that,

24:13.077 --> 24:17.748
I asked you, I said
what about the, you know,
the Russian submarine base

24:17.748 --> 24:19.375
<i>in Crimea at Sevastopol.</i>

24:19.375 --> 24:22.086
<i>He said it wasn't threatened</i>

24:22.086 --> 24:23.837
<i>by the loss of the base.</i>

24:42.439 --> 24:47.277
Even if NATO made
an agreement with Ukraine,

24:47.277 --> 24:49.655
I still don't see
the threat to Russia,

24:49.655 --> 24:53.283
in a new-- with a new,
with the new weaponry.

