30:51.016 --> 30:55.562
Last time we talked
about, uh, surveillance,
mass-surveillance.

30:55.562 --> 30:57.981
I had the impression
you were against it,

30:57.981 --> 31:00.358
and you deplored
the American technique.

31:00.358 --> 31:02.861
And as our <i>Snowden</i> movie
pointed out,

31:02.861 --> 31:06.782
it was selected targeting,
would work best on terrorists.

31:06.782 --> 31:09.367
And since that conversation,
I've been away,
coming back and I--

31:09.367 --> 31:13.413
There is a new law
in Russia that I've heard
that has been signed by you,

31:13.413 --> 31:15.999
what they call--
has been nicknamed
the Big Brother law...

31:17.584 --> 31:20.670
that provides for
mass surveillance techniques.

31:20.670 --> 31:24.633
I'm surprised. Snowden has
condemned them here, in Russia.
He's condemned them.

31:39.564 --> 31:40.107
Right.

32:24.568 --> 32:27.445
(translating)

32:48.592 --> 32:50.886
But, uh, why?
Why are you doing this?

32:50.886 --> 32:53.763
It seems like a dragnet
on all Russian citizens.

33:10.113 --> 33:11.198
Yes.

33:44.439 --> 33:46.691
So, situation-type room.

33:46.691 --> 33:48.985
This is, uh,
commando raids and stuff?

34:08.797 --> 34:11.132
What happened?

34:21.559 --> 34:23.478
(man speaking over computer)

35:01.933 --> 35:03.518
(man speaking over computer)

35:41.723 --> 35:43.475
Are those real airplanes
back there?

35:43.475 --> 35:45.727
(Putin speaking)

35:46.978 --> 35:49.564
Stone: Access
to submarines?

36:43.743 --> 36:47.789
So, in conventional
military terms, your budget,
as you said,

36:47.789 --> 36:50.709
the American budget
is 600 billion.

36:50.709 --> 36:52.961
Your annual budget is 66,

36:52.961 --> 36:54.754
according
to the Russian statistics.

36:54.754 --> 36:57.340
Sixty-six.
That's almost a tenth,

36:57.340 --> 37:00.176
uh, twelve percent roughly
of American spending.

37:00.176 --> 37:04.597
The Chinese are
at 215 billion, 215.

37:06.474 --> 37:08.393
Saudi Arabia's at 87,

37:08.393 --> 37:12.188
which leaves Russia
fourth place at 66.

37:12.188 --> 37:13.773
Is this
an accurate figure?

37:15.525 --> 37:18.361
Whoa. Saudi Arabia's spending
more money than you are.

37:21.823 --> 37:25.827
How do you do it?
I mean, you have
quite an army.

37:25.827 --> 37:29.622
I mean, quite
an intelligence economy.

37:29.622 --> 37:32.375
But what's the trick?
I mean, how do you--

37:32.375 --> 37:34.586
You don't have lobbies
that cost a lot of money?

37:34.586 --> 37:38.548
You don't--
No graft, no corruption
in this thing?

38:21.841 --> 38:22.926
The US makes a lot
out of building up.

38:22.926 --> 38:27.430
They keep talking about
its antimissile systems.

38:27.430 --> 38:28.932
Is there a reason to believe
there's been some kind
of breakthrough

38:28.932 --> 38:31.434
in their technology?

38:31.434 --> 38:33.853
Some kind of
first-strike superiority?

38:42.779 --> 38:46.950
But they have a,
they have a plan--
They're doing something.

38:46.950 --> 38:50.370
I feel that they really
are working, that they can
get an advantage

38:50.370 --> 38:54.999
in which your missile silos
would be knocked out
on a US first strike.

38:54.999 --> 38:58.002
And we'd be able to absorb
whatever you had left
to throw at us.

38:58.002 --> 39:00.630
But then we'd warn you

39:00.630 --> 39:02.674
that we're going to be hitting
you again with a second strike,

39:02.674 --> 39:06.928
and that would really wipe out
your cities, your population,
the whole works.

39:29.284 --> 39:31.828
Stone:
<i>In the matter of Syria,</i>
<i>can you describe</i>

39:31.828 --> 39:33.663
what your objective was?

39:33.663 --> 39:35.665
Give us a little history of that
and where you are now?

40:33.932 --> 40:36.392
Who's they? The terrorists.

40:36.392 --> 40:38.019
(Putin speaking)

41:01.584 --> 41:02.210
Stone:
<i>This is the biggest concern?</i>

41:02.210 --> 41:03.753
(Putin speaking)

42:14.991 --> 42:16.826
And, uh, the roads that ISIS
were using to drive

42:16.826 --> 42:20.705
<i>the trucks to, uh,</i>
<i>to Turkey, the oil trucks?</i>

42:21.164 --> 42:24.000
(Putin speaking)

42:37.847 --> 42:38.931
Stone:
<i>Right.</i>

42:46.314 --> 42:49.067
And you confronted Erdogan
with this information, correct?

42:51.778 --> 42:53.863
You were hitting
Turkmen areas,

42:53.863 --> 42:57.200
<i>and you didn't tell him,</i>
<i>uh, why?</i>

42:57.200 --> 42:59.786
(Putin speaking)

43:08.086 --> 43:11.005
Could you have said
in a diplomatic way,

43:11.005 --> 43:13.925
uh, Mr. President, uh,
we have information,
good information

43:13.925 --> 43:18.137
that the oil is coming
into certain places in Turkey,

43:18.137 --> 43:20.681
and we believe that
there are elements
in Turkey on the border,

43:20.681 --> 43:23.226
smugglers that are cooperating
with ISIS

43:23.226 --> 43:26.062
and bringing the oil in,
and we're very concerned
about that?

43:26.062 --> 43:28.731
(laughing)

43:35.863 --> 43:36.906
(translating)

44:20.324 --> 44:21.909
Who from the United States
was in that room?

