So two times a day,
tomorrow, uh, today,

44:34.672 --> 44:38.968
you'll give information to NATO
as to when the missions
are in Syria.

44:41.679 --> 44:44.182
To-- Oh, really?
Directly.

44:45.850 --> 44:47.685
And you get
the same information?

44:52.315 --> 44:54.984
To prevent
major catastrophes?

44:57.987 --> 44:59.697
Yeah. This is
a dangerous situation.

45:19.091 --> 45:21.093
Stone:
I know.

45:40.655 --> 45:42.031
So they're illegal.

45:42.031 --> 45:44.533
Any foreign troops
coming to Syria

45:44.533 --> 45:46.494
-without our invitation...
-Man: Mm-hmm.

45:46.494 --> 45:49.872
...or consultation
or permission,
they are invaders.

46:01.968 --> 46:06.055
So we have French airplanes,
we have British, uh, fighters,

46:06.055 --> 46:09.016
we have Turkish fighters,
and now we have--

46:09.016 --> 46:09.934
Is there another one
I missed?

46:18.067 --> 46:19.819
-Stone: Oh, really?
-Yeah, really so.

46:19.819 --> 46:22.488
Australians?
This is--

46:22.488 --> 46:24.407
-And Canada.
-Mm.

46:24.407 --> 46:26.742
What about Iran?
No Iranian air force?

46:28.744 --> 46:31.580
So, it's pretty hot
air space, I'd say.

46:31.580 --> 46:33.874
Putin: <i>Uh...</i> (sighs)

46:52.393 --> 46:54.478
You're making 72
to a 100 airstrikes a day?

46:54.478 --> 46:56.439
Seven days a week?

46:56.439 --> 46:57.106
-Yes. Yes.
-Wow.

46:59.817 --> 47:03.112
And, uh... (exhales)
so there must be
some progress I would think?

47:03.112 --> 47:05.406
We're not gonna have
a Vietnam-type situation here,
are we?

47:05.906 --> 47:07.408
You see progress?

48:05.758 --> 48:08.886
It seems to me
if you're striking 70
to a 120 times a day

48:08.886 --> 48:12.431
at least two months,
that's 60 days.

48:12.431 --> 48:15.810
We're down to four
to seven thousand strikes?

48:15.810 --> 48:17.061
How big is ISIS?
How big is this thing?

48:42.753 --> 48:44.088
Who's on the ground?

49:03.065 --> 49:04.650
But they don't have
Stingers?

49:08.154 --> 49:10.156
These people have fought
you before in Afghanistan.

49:14.660 --> 49:15.744
Yeah.

49:15.744 --> 49:17.079
So they were surprised?

49:19.206 --> 49:23.127
I think it'd be a good--
It's an anti-recruitment
poster for ISIS.

49:23.127 --> 49:25.463
<i>You wouldn't want to join ISIS</i>
<i>if you saw that poster.</i>

49:31.302 --> 49:34.096
(Putin speaking)

50:18.599 --> 50:19.808
Let's talk about
another war situation.

50:19.808 --> 50:22.811
In the Crimean,
when the referendum
was coming up,

50:22.811 --> 50:26.273
the US destroyer <i>Donald Cook</i>
was apparently

50:26.273 --> 50:28.442
<i>coming right into the Black Sea</i>

50:28.442 --> 50:31.362
<i>when it made a U-turn</i>
<i>and didn't carry through</i>
<i>its mission.</i>

50:31.362 --> 50:34.323
<i>It seems like it was similar</i>
<i>to the Cuban Missile Crisis</i>

50:34.323 --> 50:38.536
<i>when the same thing happened</i>
<i>where a ship was coming towards</i>

50:38.536 --> 50:40.246
<i>the demarcation line</i>
<i>and made a U-turn.</i>

51:01.141 --> 51:05.062
Rising tensions
between the US and Russia
after a Russian fighter jet

51:05.062 --> 51:07.523
<i>buzzed a US warship</i>
<i>in the Black Sea.</i>

51:07.523 --> 51:09.567
<i>ABC Chief Global Affairs</i>
<i>Correspondent Martha Raddatz</i>

51:09.567 --> 51:11.443
<i>is tracking this all</i>
<i>from Washington.</i>

51:11.443 --> 51:14.363
<i>Martha, this maneuver</i>
<i>by the Russian fighter</i>
<i>carries echoes of the Cold War.</i>

51:14.363 --> 51:17.199
It certainly does, George.
This was a Russian jet

51:17.199 --> 51:19.910
<i>that screamed by</i>
<i>a US destroyer</i>
<i>in the Black Sea,</i>

51:19.910 --> 51:23.038
<i>not just once</i>
<i>but 12 times</i>

51:23.038 --> 51:24.957
<i>over a</i>
<i>90-minute period.</i>

51:24.957 --> 51:28.168
(Russian newsman speaking)

51:42.308 --> 51:43.726
(Putin speaking)

51:43.726 --> 51:45.060
Stone:
Yeah.

51:53.527 --> 51:56.280
(translator speaking)

52:04.705 --> 52:05.247
Bastion,
was it called?

52:08.250 --> 52:11.086
Stone: <i>But this</i>
<i>is a big missile.</i>

52:11.086 --> 52:14.923
<i>And the destroyer,</i>
<i>the</i> Donald Cook
<i>has Tomahawk missiles.</i>

52:14.923 --> 52:16.675
(Putin speaking)

52:21.013 --> 52:22.222
Stone:
<i>That's probably why</i>
<i>it turned around.</i>

52:22.222 --> 52:25.643
But your commander had
the authority to fire.

52:25.643 --> 52:27.353
(Putin speaking)

52:34.735 --> 52:36.278
Stone: <i>Still,</i>
<i>it's a big incident,</i>
<i>potentially.</i>

52:47.247 --> 52:50.376
What time frame did
all this take place?
This challenge?

53:41.677 --> 53:43.345
Was he warned? Was there
a warning sent out to him?

53:50.185 --> 53:52.020
All this thing takes place
in two minutes?

53:52.020 --> 53:53.522
Thirty minutes?
Fifty minutes?

53:56.316 --> 53:59.194
I mean, does this
happen all the time?

53:59.194 --> 54:00.863
He sounds very cool.

54:00.863 --> 54:03.240
Were you... (chuckles)
Were you contacted?

54:12.374 --> 54:13.542
He admits to the brink.

54:16.336 --> 54:19.214
Well, finally,
you're admitting it.

54:26.722 --> 54:28.682
Stone: Yeah.

54:33.562 --> 54:34.438
Yes.

54:42.237 --> 54:44.656
At that time,
you made a speech.

54:44.656 --> 54:47.743
"This is our historic territory.
These are Russian people.

54:47.743 --> 54:50.579
<i>"They are in danger now.</i>

54:50.579 --> 54:53.248
<i>"We can't leave them alone.</i>

54:53.248 --> 54:55.542
<i>"It wasn't us</i>
<i>who staged the coup,</i>

54:55.542 --> 54:57.252
<i>"it was done by nationalists</i>

54:57.252 --> 54:59.963
<i>"and people</i>
<i>with far-right views.</i>

54:59.963 --> 55:03.300
<i>"You supported them.</i>
<i>But where do you live?</i>

55:03.300 --> 55:05.469
<i>"Five thousand miles away.</i>

55:05.469 --> 55:09.139
"But we live here,
and it is our land.

55:09.139 --> 55:11.600
"What do you want
to fight for there?

55:11.600 --> 55:14.061
<i>"You don't know, do you?</i>
<i>But we do know.</i>

55:14.061 --> 55:15.729
<i>And we are ready for it."</i>

55:17.231 --> 55:19.316
Stone:
<i>Is there any hope?</i>

55:42.005 --> 55:43.423
So he's an optimist.

55:46.009 --> 55:48.178
(translator speaks)

57:16.725 --> 57:18.810
Or Moscow will be
a caliphate.

57:21.271 --> 57:22.981
(both laugh)

57:24.232 --> 57:26.068
Thank you.

57:26.068 --> 57:28.528
Well, you came close.

57:28.528 --> 57:30.614
And now you're close again,
so it seems to be

57:30.614 --> 57:33.075
a very tense presidency
you have.

57:33.075 --> 57:34.993
(chuckles)

57:34.993 --> 57:38.205
(sighs)

